-- Ingersoll-Rand revenue rises 4.3 pct on higher cooling systems demand 
-- By Rohit T. K. in Bangalore
-- Tue Jul 22, 2014 07:24AM EDT
-- None



July 22 (Reuters) - Ingersoll-Rand Plc <IR.N>, the maker of Trane airconditioners, reported a 4.3 rise in quarterly revenue, driven by higher demand for its heating and cooling systems.

Revenue rose to $3.54 billion in the second quarter ended June 30, from $3.40 billion a year earlier. [ID:nBw9L2kXBa]